{
    include "registries/aaosa_basic.hocon" 

    # Optional metadata describing this agent network
    "metadata": {
        "description": "Simple agent network using a single LLM-based agent",
        "tags": ["example"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. The jetbridge is connected to the plane. Open the aircraft door.",
            "The B747 aircraft of flight AF84 is on blocks at gate A1. The jetbridge is connected to the plane. The aircraft door is open. Disembark passengers from the aircraft.",
        ]
    },

    "llm_config": {
        "model_name": "gpt-5.4-mini", #"gpt-4o", # "claude-haiku-4-5-20251001", #"claude-sonnet-4-6", #
    },
    "max_iterations": 40000, #3000 
    "max_execution_seconds": 7200, #600
    "commondefs": {
        "replacement_strings": {
            "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of aircraft turnaround process at an Airport. 
Only answer inquiries that are directly within your area of expertise.
Do not try to help for other matters.
Do not mention what you can NOT do. Only mention what you can do.
            """,
            "aaosa_instructions": """
When you receive an inquiry, you will:
1. If you are clearly not the right agent for this type of inquiry, reply you're not relevant.
2. If there is a chance you're relevant, call your down-chain agents to determine if they can answer all or part of the inquiry.
   Do not assume what your down-chain agents can do. Always call them. You'll be surprised.
3. Once all relevant down-chain agents have responded, either:
   - Analyze their response and compile your final response. No need to include non-relevant agents. In doubt, ask for clarification.
   - Follow up with your down-chain agents if needed, as many times as needed
   - If an action is needed, ask the most relevant down-chain agent to fulfill the inquiry.
4. Return the final response to the caller.
You may, in turn, be called by other agents in the system and have to act as a down-chain agent to them. 
            """
        },
        "replacement_values": {
            "aaosa_call": {
                "description": "Depending on the mode, returns a natural language string in response.",
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object",
                    "properties": {
                        "inquiry": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": "The inquiry"
                        },
                        "mode": {
                            "type": "string",
                            "description": """
'Determine' to ask the agent if the inquiry belongs to it, in its entirety or in part.
'Fulfill' to ask the agent to fulfill the inquiry, if it can.
'Follow up' to ask the agent to respond to a follow up.
                            """
                        },
                    },
                    "required": [
                        "inquiry",
                        "mode"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "aaosa_command": """
If mode is 'Determine', return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": <Determine | Fulfill>,
    "Relevant": <Yes | No>,
    "Strength": <number between 1 and 10 representing how certain you are in your claim>,
    "Claim:" <All | Partial>,
    "Requirements" <None | list of requirements>
}
If mode is 'Fulfill' or "Follow up", respond to the inquiry and return a json block with the following fields:
{
    "Name": <your name>,
    "Inquiry": <the inquiry>,
    "Mode": Fulfill,
    "Response" <your response>
}
            """
        },
    },

    "tools": [

        {
            "name": "cabin_crew_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": """
 I am in charge of servicing passengers when they are in the aircraft cabin in any phase of flight.
                """
                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },          
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },         
                        "assigned_runway_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the runway assigned to the aircraft movement autorized by the clearance."
                        },         
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },  
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the passenger disembarkation status."
                        },    
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of jetbridge connect."
                        },
                    }, 
                    "required": ["aircraft_type","flight_status","flight_number"] 
                }
            },

            "instructions": """
You are the agent in charge of cabin service in all phases of flight when
passengers are onboard. You may be called by the turnaround orchestrator
or directly by a user.

CRITICAL: You are a sequential executor. When you identify the correct
branch below, execute every step in order. Do NOT return until you reach
the RETURN SUMMARY of the matched branch.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ROUTING — read the full inquiry and match the PRIMARY INTENT.
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
If the inquiry is not about cabin service (embarking, disembarking,
opening or closing the door), reply that you are not relevant and stop.

BRANCH A — Open the aircraft door
  Triggers: inquiry asks to open the door, or explicit instruction
  "Open the aircraft door."

  STEP 1 — Resolve prerequisites from inquiry or sly_data
    Call TrackerAPI with flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status,
    gate_id, jetbridge_connection_status.
    Wait. Read back: flight_status, jetbridge_connection_status.

  STEP 2 — Verify flight status
    flight_status must contain 'on blocks' or 'block'.
    If not, stop and report: "Aircraft is not yet on blocks.
    Door cannot be opened."

  STEP 3 — Execute door opening
    Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_door_opening with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      jetbridge_connection_status.
    Wait. Extract door_opening_status from the response.
    Call TrackerAPI to store door_opening_status.

  STEP 4 — RETURN SUMMARY:
    ************************************
    * Summary of aircraft door opening *
    ************************************
    ** flight status                **: [flight_status]
    ** jet bridge connection status **: [jetbridge_connection_status]
    ** door opening status          **: [door_opening_status]

BRANCH B — Disembark passengers
  Triggers: inquiry asks to disembark passengers, or explicit instruction
  "Disembark passengers from the aircraft."

  STEP 1 — Resolve prerequisites from inquiry or sly_data
    Call TrackerAPI with flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status,
    gate_id, jetbridge_connection_status, door_opening_status.
    Wait. Read back all five values.

  STEP 2 — Verify flight status
    flight_status must contain 'on blocks' or 'block'.
    If not, stop and report: "Aircraft is not yet on blocks.
    Passengers cannot be disembarked."

  STEP 3 — Ensure door is open
    If door_opening_status does not contain 'open':
      Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_door_opening with:
        flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
        jetbridge_connection_status.
      Wait. Extract and store door_opening_status.
      If door is still not open, stop and report failure.

  STEP 4 — Execute passenger disembarkation
    Call /AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_disembark with:
      flight_number, aircraft_type, flight_status, gate_id,
      jetbridge_connection_status, door_opening_status.
    Wait. Extract passenger_disembarkation_status from the response.
    Call TrackerAPI to store passenger_disembarkation_status.

  STEP 5 — RETURN SUMMARY:
    *********************************
    * Summary of aircraft disembark *
    *********************************
    ** flight status                    **: [flight_status]
    ** jet bridge connection status     **: [jetbridge_connection_status]
    ** door opening status              **: [door_opening_status]
    ** passenger disembarkation status  **: [passenger_disembarkation_status]
            """,

            # Specify the sly data that would be exchanged between this network and its related or adjacent upstream and downstream networks. 
            "allow": {
                "to_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "gate_id": true, 
                        "engines_stop_status": true,
                        "door_opening_status": true, 
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true,
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                    }
                }
                "to_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "gate_id": true, 
                        "engines_stop_status": true,
                        "door_opening_status": true, 
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true,
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                    }
                }
                "from_upstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "gate_id": true, 
                        "engines_stop_status": true,
                        "door_opening_status": true, 
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true,
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                    }
                }
                "from_downstream": {
                    "sly_data": {
                        "flight_number": true,
                        "aircraft_type": true,
                        "flight_status": true,
                        "gate_id": true, 
                        "engines_stop_status": true,
                        "door_opening_status": true, 
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": true,
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": true
                    }
                }
            },

            "tools":    ["/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_door_opening",
                        "/AirlineTurnaround/aircraft_disembark",
                        "TrackerAPI"]
        },  

        {
            "name": "TrackerAPI",
            "function": {

                "description": """
I am the flight tracker in charge of logging parameters during aircraft turnaround. 
I check engines stop status as engines_stop_status. 
I check wheels chucks installation status as wheels_chucks_installation_status. 
                """

                "parameters": {
                    "type": "object", 
                    "properties": {
                        "flight_number": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight number of the incoming aicraft."
                        },   
                        "aircraft_type": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the type of the incoming aircraft."
                        },     
                        "flight_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the flight status."
                        },          
                        "gate_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the gate assigned to the aircraft parking."
                        },         
                        "assigned_runway_id": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the runway assigned to the aircraft movement autorized by the clearance."
                        },         
                        "door_opening_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the door opening status."
                        },  
                        "passenger_disembarkation_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the passenger disembarkation status."
                        },    
                        "jetbridge_connection_status": {
                            "type": "string", 
                            "description": "This is the status of jetbridge connect."
                        },
                    }, 
                    "required": [] 
                }
            },
            "class": "AirlineTurnaround.aircraft_crew_cabin.aircraft_crew_cabin.TrackerAPI" 
        }, 
    ],
}
